<title>USA: Spartan Motors insiders buy 12,000 shares.</title>
<headline>Spartan Motors insiders buy 12,000 shares.</headline>
<dateline>CHARLOTTE, Mich. 1997-02-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Spartan Motors Inc said Monday that two insiders purchased a total of 12,000 shares of its stock within the last six weeks.</p>
<p>The manufacturer of custom chassis for motorhomes, fire trucks and transit buses said the open market stock purchases were made by chief financial officer Richard Schalter and director of operations John Williamson.</p>
<p>Both individuals joined Spartan in the fourth quarter of 1996.</p>
